SAFT, a unit of Cie Generaled'Electricite of France, said it bought U.K.-based Alcad Ltdfrom Penn Central Corp's Marathon Manufacturing Cos Inc.    Terms of the deal were not disclosed.    Alcad is one of the world's largest producers ofpocket-plate nickel-cadmium storeage batteries, used inindustrial and railroad applications to start engines and aslight sources, SAFT said.    SAFT said it expects to add 400 jobs at the U.K.operations. Reuter&#3;